<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1104068002">
<title>
Circuit Description
</title>
<ptxt>
When ignition is set to ON, the main relay turns on (contacts close) and the main power is supplied to ECM. ECM then supplies 5 V power to the following sensors: A/C refrigerant pressure sensor, APP sensor, TP sensor and electric load current sensor.
</ptxt>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A1104068003">
<title>
Troubleshooting
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Before troubleshooting, be sure to read “Precautions for ECM Circuit Inspection” under 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A1000001">Precautions for Engine</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Before performing, be sure to confirm that related fuses of ECM power circuit have not blown out.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If any fuse has blown out, replace the fuse and check circuits connected to the blown fuse for short circuit to ground.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<diag type = "test" id = "AENBP70A1104068004">
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068005">
<title>
Battery check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that battery voltage is 12 V or more.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 2.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Check battery and generator referring to 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A1A04001">Battery Inspection</intxref>
 and 
<intxref refid = "AENBP70A1A04003">Generator Test</intxref>
.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068006">
<title>
Main relay power supply check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
With ignition OFF, remove main relay (1) from individual circuit fuse box No.1.
</ptxt>
<testfigure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A111039.swf" width = "90.000mm" height = "44.484mm" ver = "02" gw = "157" gh = "110"/>
</testfigure>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to main relay connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, set ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between each of “F1” and “F2” circuit and ground is battery voltage.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 3.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Check that “FI” fuse has not blown. If check result is OK, repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068007">
<title>
Main relay check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check main relay. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306019"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 4.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Replace main relay.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068008">
<title>
Ignition mode circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
With ignition OFF, install main relay to individual circuit fuse box No.1.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect “C01” and “E01” connectors from ECM.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to “C01” and “E01” connectors.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, set ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between “G1” and ground is battery voltage.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 5.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Check that “IG COIL” fuse or “IG1 SIG” fuse has not blown. If check result is OK, repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068009">
<title>
Main relay drive circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between “E1” and ground is battery voltage.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 6.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068010">
<title>
Main power supply circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Using service wire, ground “E1”.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between each of “E2” and “E3” circuit and ground is battery voltage.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 7.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068011">
<title>
ECM ground circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Set ignition OFF.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that resistance between each of “H1”, “H2” and “H3” circuit and ground is less than 1 Ω.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Go to Step 8.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Repair or replace defective wire harness.
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
<testgroup id = "AENBP70A1104068012">
<title>
Sensor power supply circuit check
</title>
<test1>
<ptxt>
With ignition OFF, connect “C01” and “E01” connectors to ECM.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect connectors from APP sensor, electric load current sensor, electric throttle body assembly and A/C refrigerant pressure sensor.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check for proper terminal connection to each sensor connector.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
If connections are OK, set ignition ON.
</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>
Check that voltage between each of the following circuits and ground is approx. 5 V.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
A1
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
A2
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
B1
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
C1
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
D1
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</test1>
<question>
Is check result OK?
</question>
<result type = "yes"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
ECM power supply and ground circuit is in good condition.
</ptxt>
</action>
<result type = "no"/>
<action>
<ptxt>
Check wiring harness for open, short circuit to battery and short circuit to ground. If wiring harness is in good condition, replace ECM and recheck ECM power supply and ground circuit. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A1306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</action>
</testgroup>
</diag>
